@startuml I2C_State_Machine
title I2C Driver — Master Transaction State Machine
' NOTE: modeled on the standard STM32F4 I2C register sequence
' (CR1/CR2/SR1/SR2/DR) and the same RCC-owning constructor pattern
' used by the other drivers. Verify against actual I2C_Driver.h/.cpp.

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #F5FAFF
    BorderColor #2C7FB8
    ArrowColor #2C7FB8
}

[*] --> Idle

Idle --> GenStart : start()\nCR1.START = 1
GenStart --> AddressPhase : poll SR1.SB set

AddressPhase --> AddrAck : write DR = (7-bit addr << 1) | R/W
AddrAck --> TransferData : poll SR1.ADDR,\nread SR1+SR2 to clear

state TransferData {
  [*] --> Writing : if Write
  [*] --> Reading : if Read

  Writing --> Writing : write(data)\nwrite DR, poll SR1.TXE
  Writing --> [*] : all bytes sent,\npoll SR1.BTF

  Reading --> Reading : read()\npoll SR1.RXNE, read DR
  Reading --> [*] : last byte:\nNACK + STOP before final read
}

TransferData --> GenStop : stop()\nCR1.STOP = 1
GenStop --> Idle

Idle --> Idle : isBusBusy()\ncheck SR2.BUSY

note right of AddrAck
  NACK on address (SR1.AF set)
  means device not present —
  driver should clear AF and
  generate STOP.
end note

@enduml
